CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 7, 1956, pg. A14 reads: "Gas From Coal - Richard Graves (right), chemical engineer with the Bureau of Mines near South Park, and technician David Williams discuss a small section of the plant which Graves is rebuilding to produce cheap, but good gasoline from coal.- Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: David Williams, holding clipboard, and Richard Graves, standing in natural gas plant
